##Setting up Eclipse for threads##

Step#1
Go to Project -> Properties -> C/C++ Build -> Settings
In the Language Standard drop down box, 
select: "ISO C++11 (-std=c++0x)"
and then apply changes.

Step#2
Go to Project -> Properties -> C/C++ General -> Paths and Symbols.
Select the Libraries tab,
click Add and type: "pthread"
and then apply changes.

Step#3
Go to Window -> Preferences -> C/C++ -> Build -> Settings
Select the Discovery tab, and then click CDT GCC Built-in Compiler Settings.
Append -std=c++11 in box at bottom
and then apply changes.

Step#4
Go to Project -> Index -> Rebuild.

And That's it!!
You are good to write code with pthreads.......
